      • getADMD

        public java.lang.String getADMD()
        Description copied from interface: Name
        Gets the administration management domain name (ADMD) component of a hierarchical name (A=).

        This property returns an empty string for a hierarchical name with no ADMD component.

        This property returns an empty string for an Internet or flat name.

        A name created through Domino administration does not contain a ADMD component.

        Returns:
        The A= part of the name

      • getAbbreviated

        public java.lang.String getAbbreviated()
        Description copied from interface: Name
        A hierarchical name in abbreviated form.
        Returns:
        The abbreviated name. If the abbreviated name would be ambiguous or contains non-domino components then the canonical name is returned.

      • getAddr821

        public java.lang.String getAddr821()
        Description copied from interface: Name
        IP address in the format based on RFC 821 Address Format Syntax.

        The RFC 821 address is a name followed by an at sign followed by an organization, for example, jbgoode@acme.us.com. In an RFC 822 address, it is the part enclosed in pointed brackets.

        Returns:
        The RFC821 Address. If there is none then an empty string is returned.
